Stay-At-Home-Student OOTD. Dogs included. I swear if you walked into my house you’d take one look at me and think I do nothing all day…but I’ll be finishing my Bachelors in a total 2.5 years instead of 4 so 💁🏼‍♀️ You can do this by 1) Finding a school that does shorter terms so you can fit more into a year (8/10 week classes). 2) Taking CLEP exams, and ACE credit classes from places like Straighter Lines and Sophia. 3)Obviously this only works if you’re easily self motivated and have a relatively open schedule. I feel like a lot of people who are considering going back to school at an older age can benefit from this!

With 2.5 weeks of school left I pulled Trey out. He has been relentlessly bullied and harassed for the last two years by the same few kids. Aside from apologies, the school has done nothing about it. The final straw came last Friday when he was physically assaulted twice in the same day. We got no incident report despite Trey asking a teacher for help. That was the seventh time he has been physically assaulted at this school.  SO to cheer him up we are taking a trip to see the grandparents😁 I have no idea where he and Carter are going to school next year, but I can definitely say where they won’t be going.

I’m so proud of this kid. He started at a new school this year due to major bullying at his last school. His new school is amazing. He’s thriving. He no longer comes home crying, and he’s able to sleep at night. Maybe I’ll tell the story of the other school one day. Just have to make sure all the legal ends are tight. For now, parents, trust your gut.

I’ve been working on refurbishing an old steamer wardrobe trunk from the early 1900s. I have zero experience doing this but it has been fun so far. Today I was cleaning some broken hardware that I removed from the trunk—as a way to figure out what the best method is. I was disappointed to find out that under the beautiful brass color is some bland steel. BUT ITS FINE🤣ps- I post a few updates about this project on my stories most days!
